<br>
12-25 - East Karana... easy to beg/buy an SOW and once you have that charm is your best friend.  At 16, just trade Breeze for SOW.  Fight near gorge at first, once Crags are even-yella you can charm them.<br>
<br>
25-40 - Sol A... Most ppl in range to hunt here dont.  Keep Mez, Color Shift, Color Skew, Charm, Tash, Rune, Root and Nuke loaded.  Lots of double spawns here.  Rune up, mez one, other will charge.  C. Shift, Mez 2nd one.  Tash first, charm, pet attack 2nd.  When charm breaks and they both charge you, Color Shift, Color Skew, Re-charm, /pet attack.  And dont let ppl tell you that Sol A isnt xp at 40.  I coulda stayed til probably 42 killing around King, but moved to:<br>
<br>
41-52 - Sol B... Zone in thru Sol A, near pool room.  Same basic plan as Sol A, and all the GKs in this area can be pulled in pairs.  There are 2 singles, 1 in hall near pool and another that wanders between the Sol A zone areas.  Just wait for wanderer to leave, pull 2 in room up ramp to zone and let em fight.  You have time before wanderer comes again.  Then fight wanderer vs. hall spawn.  Then pull 2 from pool room.  If you have time, before 1st room re-spawns you can pull either side room.<br>
<br>
52-56 - Tim Deep... Raptors.  Larger Isle has lots of double spawns.  Given the option Charm Vicious Raptor, he can take 2 normal raptors easy.  Occasionally you'll need to pull an extra from other isle, but normally pretty easy.<br>
<br>
FYI - Been a while since I played chanter, but that's how I solo'd almost my whole time.  Only grouped for raids and ports.  Not sure how you'd do in Velious, Kunark was the only thing available to me.  Also, color shift and skew I may have mixed.  Use 3 sec one first, then 7 sec one.  You have time if you're quick to get both off before mobs can touch you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/usnoish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snoish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(2/6/02 11:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=226.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> Ulthorks in EW are plentiful, and charm works well. Good at 35-40 ish<br>
